</string>
    </property>
    <property name="html">
     <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;Jose Rizal was born to                                         and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;                                       , who were highly influential in shaping his intellect and character. His father, Francisco, was a prosperous tenant-farmer of a Dominican-owned hacienda. He was described as industrious, principled, and well-educated, despite not having formal schooling. Teodora, on the other hand, was an educated woman from an illustrious family. She was known for her intelligence, strong will, and piety. A great influence on Rizal's intellectual development, Teodora served as his first teacher, teaching him to read and write at an early age.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot; style=&quot; margin-top:12px; margin-bottom:12px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;&quot;&gt;The family name &amp;quot;Rizal&amp;quot; was adopted by the family to avoid persecution due to their ties with the Filipino reformist movement. Originally, they used the surname &amp;quot;Mercado,&amp;quot; but to protect their business interests and avoid suspicion, they changed it to Rizal, which means &amp;quot;green fields&amp;quot; in Spanish.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
